org.apache.ambari.server.state.kerberos

Class KerberosDescriptor

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.ambari.server.state.kerberos.AbstractKerberosDescriptor
      • org.apache.ambari.server.state.kerberos.AbstractKerberosDescriptorContainer
        • org.apache.ambari.server.state.kerberos.KerberosDescriptor

  • public class KerberosDescriptor
extends AbstractKerberosDescriptorContainer
    KerberosDescriptor is an implementation of an AbstractKerberosDescriptorContainer that encapsulates an entire Kerberos descriptor hierarchy.

    A KerberosDescriptor has the following properties:

    • services
    • properties
    • identities (AbstractKerberosDescriptorContainer)
    • configurations (AbstractKerberosDescriptorContainer)

    The following (pseudo) JSON Schema will yield a valid KerberosDescriptor 

       {
      "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-04/schema#",
      "title": "KerberosDescriptor",
      "description": "Describes a Kerberos descriptor",
      "type": "object",
      "properties": {
        "services": {
          "description": "A list of service descriptors",
          "type": "array",
          "items": {
            "title": "KerberosServiceDescriptor"
            "type": "KerberosServiceDescriptor"
          }
        },
        "properties": {
          "description": "Global properties that can be used in variable replacements",
          "type": "object",
          "patternProperties": {
            "^[\w\.\_]?$": {}"
          }
        }
        "identities": {
          "description": "A list of Kerberos identity descriptors",
          "type": "array",
          "items": {
            "title": "KerberosIdentityDescriptor"
            "type": "KerberosIdentityDescriptor"
          }
        },
        "configurations": {
          "description": "A list of relevant configuration blocks",
          "type": "array",
          "items": {
            "title": "KerberosConfigurationDescriptor"
            "type": "KerberosConfigurationDescriptor"
          }
        }
      }
   }

    In this implementation, AbstractKerberosDescriptor.name will be null

      • principals

        public Map<String,String> principals()
                              throws org.apache.ambari.server.AmbariException
        Get a map of principals, where the key is the principal path (SERVICE/COMPONENT/principal_name or SERVICE/principal_name) and the value is the principal.

        For example if the kerberos principal of the HISTORYSERVER is defined in the kerberos.json: "name": "history_server_jhs", "principal": { "value": "jhs/_HOST@${realm}", "type" : "service", }, Then "jhs/_HOST@EXAMPLE.COM" will be put into the map under the "MAPREDUCE2/HISTORYSERVER/history_server_jhs" key.

        Throws:
        org.apache.ambari.server.AmbariException
